STEP1:
df = (
    spark.readStream
    .format("cloudFiles")   #Tells Databricks to use Auto Loader for incremental file ingestion
    .option("cloudFiles.format", "csv")
    .option("cloudFiles.schemaLocation", schema_path) #to store schema of our data,useful when upcoming files have newly col
    .option("header", "true")
    .option("cloudFiles.inferColumnTypes", "true") #to detect schema,col data type
    .load(source_path)
)


By this code, Auto Loader picks files from ADLS Gen2 landing path.

STEP2:
from pyspark.sql.functions import current_timestamp, input_file_name

df_final = (
    df
    .withColumn("ingestion_timestamp", current_timestamp()) #to know when the record was loaded into Databricks.
    .withColumn("source_file_path", input_file_name()) #to know from which source file each record came.
)

This is useful for:

Audit tracking
Debugging
Data lineage
Reprocessing failed/bad files
Identifying source of wrong records

This step is used to add audit columns like ingestion timestamp and source file path to each record before writing into the Delta table.

STEP3:

query = (
    df_final.writeStream
    .format("delta")
    .option("checkpointLocation", checkpoint_path)
    .outputMode("append")
    .trigger(availableNow=True)
    .toTable(target_table) or .start(bronze_path)-> this will write data in adlsgen2
)

“The last step is writeStream, where we write the Auto Loader output into a Delta table. We provide checkpointLocation so Databricks tracks already processed files and loads only new files in the next run.

stores checkpoint metadata. This is very important because checkpoint helps Auto Loader remember which files are already processed. Auto Loader stores file-processing metadata in the checkpoint location and uses it to provide exactly-once processing

means process all currently available new files and then stop automatically. This is useful when running the notebook through a scheduled Databricks Job. Databricks recommends Trigger.AvailableNow for triggered incremental jobs where continuous low-latency streaming is not required



NOTE:-
.option("cloudFiles.useManagedFileEvents", "true")->add this step in read files step1

Auto Loader uses managed file events.
That means when a new file lands in ADLS/external storage, Databricks uses file event metadata to know that a new file arrived. Auto Loader can then discover new files from the file events cache instead of doing full directory listing every time.

USECASE:-if your source folder has thousands or millions of files, listing becomes slower and costly.

enabling File arrival trigger in Databricks Job UI allows the job to run automatically when a new file arrives.


.option("cloudFiles.useNotifications", "true")-->cloud itself send notification  through queue service whenever the new 
file landed in source
